This paper deals with the concept of differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses probability density functions and probability mass functions, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the attacker's goal of guessing specific attributes, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB).
